timeline.body:
You could simplify these bits here (and in several other places) by writing the whole header after the content.

For example, if the method `void computeHeader(byte[] buffer, int initialPos, int contentSize)` writes only the header, then writing the content could become something like:
```java
        int pos = initialPos + LINE_RECORD_HEADER_SIZE;
        for (FileBlock fileBlock : fileBlocks) {
            highAddr = Math.max(highAddr, fileBlock.getHighAddr());
            pos = fileBlock.computeContents(buffer, pos);
        }
        computeHeader(initialPos, buffer, highAddr);
        return pos;
```

