timeline.body:
What do you think about `CVLineRecord` deciding if we need a new file?

It already contains the necessary data, so adding a method (e.g., `maybeAddNewFile`) that would add a new file and return `true` only if the new `fileId` differs from the `fileId` of the current `FileBlock` should be easy.

That would allow this method to be simplified as follows (and you could also completely remove `previousRange` processing).
```suggestion
        FileEntry file = cvDebugInfo.findFile(range.getFileAsPath());
        if (file == null) {
            debug("processRange: range has no file: %s\n", range);
            return;
        }

        if (range.getLine() == -1) {
            debug("processRange: ignoring: bad line number\n");
            return;
        }

        if (lineRecord.maybeAddNewFile(file)) {
            debug("processRange: added new file: %s\n", file);
        }
```

